casebody.data:
DOVENMUEHLE MORTGAGE, INC., Appellant,
v.
UNDERWRITERS AT LLOYD'S, London, (AFB Syndicate Nos. 2623 and 623), Respondent. No. ED 106566 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION FOUR. Filed: December 26, 2018 Eugene J. Brockland, Jr., Brian M. Wacker, 120 S. Central Ave. Ste. 700, St. Louis, MO 63105, For Plaintiff/Appellant. Anthony R. Behr, Andrew T. Tangaro, Joel O. Christensen, 7777 Bonhomme Ave. Ste. 1400, Clayton, MO 63105, For Defendant/Respondent. Before Kurt S. Odenwald, P.J., Gary M. Gaertner, Jr., J., and Colleen Dolan, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Dovenmuehle Mortgage, Inc. appeals the trial court's grant of summary judgment in favor of Underwriters at Lloyd's, London. Finding that the trial court did not err in granting summary judgment, we affirm the judgment of the trial court.

No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. However, we have provided the parties a memorandum setting forth the reasons for our decision. The judgment of the trial court is affirmed under Rule 84.16(b).
